**Probability of same color:**

The probability of drawing two balls of the same color is:
P(same color) = P(both red) + P(both blue)

P(both red) = (8/15) × (x/(x+9))

P(both blue) = (7/15) × (9/(x+9))

**Setting up the equation:**

$$\frac{8}{15} \cdot \frac{x}{x+9} + \frac{7}{15} \cdot \frac{9}{x+9} = \frac{151}{300}$$

