Problem: 6.3-5. Let $Y_1 < Y_2 < \cdots < Y_8$ be the order statistics of eight independent observations from a continuous-type distribution with 70 th percentile $\pi_{0.7}=27.3$.
(a) Determine $P\left(Y_7<27.3\right)$.
 The unit of the answer should be  .
Solution: I need to find P(Y₇ < 27.3), where Y₇ is the 7th order statistic out of 8 observations, and 27.3 is the 70th percentile of the distribution.

**Key Information:**
- We have 8 observations: Y₁ < Y₂ < ... < Y₈
- π₀.₇ = 27.3 (the 70th percentile)
- This means P(X < 27.3) = 0.7 for any single observation X

**Finding P(Y₇ < 27.3):**

Y₇ < 27.3 means that the 7th order statistic is less than 27.3.

This is equivalent to saying: at most 6 observations are greater than or equal to 27.3, or equivalently, at least 7 observations are less than 27.3.

Actually, let me reconsider: Y₇ < 27.3 means that at least 7 of the 8 observations are less than 27.3.

For each observation X, we have:
- P(X < 27.3) = 0.7
- P(X ≥ 27.3) = 0.3

Y₇ < 27.3 occurs when at least 7 out of 8 observations fall below 27.3.

This happens when:
- Exactly 7 observations are below 27.3, OR
- All 8 observations are below 27.3

Using the binomial distribution with n = 8, p = 0.7:

P(Y₇ < 27.3) = P(at least 7 successes) = P(X = 7) + P(X = 8)

where X ~ Binomial(8, 0.7)

P(X = 7) = C(8,7) × (0.7)⁷ × (0.3)¹
= 8 × (0.7)⁷ × 0.3
= 8 × 0.0823543 × 0.3
= 0.197649

P(X = 8) = C(8,8) × (0.7)⁸ × (0.3)⁰
= 1 × (0.7)⁸ × 1
= 0.05764801

P(Y₇ < 27.3) = 0.197649 + 0.05764801
= 0.25529701

Rounding to a reasonable number of significant figures: 0.255 or approximately 0.26

