- P(H|I) = 0.35
- P(I|N) = 0.11

First, I'll find P(N):
P(H) + P(N) + P(L) = 1
0.16 + P(N) + 0.19 = 1
P(N) = 0.65

Now I'll use P(H|I) = 0.35 to find P(H and I):
P(H and I) = P(H|I) × P(I) = 0.35 × 0.17 = 0.0595

Next, I'll use P(I|N) = 0.11 to find P(I and N):
